{
  "texts": [
    "Explaining the moral development of LLMs through the lens of Dewey's moral philosophy is only an initial step toward a comprehensive interpretive framework.",
    "The absence of a unified theory for human cognitive abilities and consciousness, coupled with a lack of theoretical explanations for intrinsic mechanisms involving emergence and homogenization in LLMs, complicates the interpretation of LLM's moral capabilities.",
    "Achieving genuine ethical AI will require ongoing collaboration among engineers, philosophers, policy-makers, and societal stakeholders.",
    "Dewey discusses the growth of habit and morality at various stages in his works.",
    "Generally, instinct precedes habit, with instinct being primarily driven by impulses."
  ]
}